%26quot%3B%20Schueler%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bad%20guys%20are%20getting%20really%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20Chris%20Risley%2C%20CEO%20of%20wireless%20threat%20intelligence%20company%20Bastille%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20threat%20landscape%20changes%2C%20cybersecurity%20jobs%20are%20in%20high%20demand%20as%20companies%20and%20governments%20seek%20to%20safeguard%20against%20AI-fueled%20cyberattacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20employed%20information%20security%20analysts%2C%20who%20focus%20on%20protecting%20computer%20systems%2C%20is%20expected%20to%20grow%2033%25%20between%202023%20and%202033%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fooh%2Fcomputer-and-information-technology%2Finformation-security-analysts.htm%3Futm_source%3Dchatgpt.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20US%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20conversations%20with%20Business%20Insider%2C%20more%20than%20half%20a%20dozen%20cybersecurity%20executives%20explained%20why%20demand%20for%20cybersecurity%20roles%20has%20grown%20and%20how%20the%20security%20concerns%20facing%20companies%20have%20evolved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20Caron%2C%20head%20of%20cybersecurity%20of%20Americas%20at%20global%20corporate%20intelligence%20and%20cybersecurity%20consultancy%20S-RM%2C%20said%20that%20attackers%20are%20using%20AI%20to%20%26quot%3Bbetter%20understand%20behavioral%20analytics%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20the%20time%20someone%20logs%20into%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDanny%20Jenkins%2C%20the%20CEO%2C%20and%20cofounder%20of%20cybersecurity%20platform%20ThreatLocker%2C%20said%20that%20AI%20also%20opened%20the%20door%20to%20anyone%20with%20a%20computer%20being%20able%20to%20create%20malicious%20software.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTwo%20years%20ago%2C%20if%20you%20wanted%20to%20write%20a%20piece%20of%20malware%2C%20you%20had%20to%20be%20skilled%20enough%20to%20write%20malware%2C%26quot%3B%20Jenkins%2C%20whose%20company%20has%20clients%20including%20Jet%20Blue%2C%20told%20BI%2C%20adding%20that%20you%20%26quot%3Bno%20longer%20need%20to%20be%20a%20smart%20engineer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20tools%20have%20also%20made%20it%20easier%20for%20traditional%20phishing%20scams%20to%20mask%20some%20of%20the%C2%A0usual%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffake-remote-job-offer-scam-text-interview-signs-equipment-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ered%20flags%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20detectable%20spelling%20errors%C2%A0or%20poorly%20constructed%20messages.%20It's%20also%20advanced%20newer%20attack%20methods%20for%20bad%20actors%2C%20like%20deepfakes%2C%20with%20AI-powered%20audio%20and%20video.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20I%20need%20is%20one%20good%20picture%20of%20your%20face%2C%20and%20I%20can%20run%20a%20deepfake%20video%20on%20you%20within%2020%20minutes%2C%26quot%3B%20Schueler%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMike%20Britton%2C%20chief%20information%20officer%20for%20Abnormal%20Security%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20evolution%20of%20the%20digital%20age%20has%20also%20allowed%20bad%20actors%20to%20attack%20from%20virtually%20anywhere%20around%20the%20globe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20essentially%20taken%20a%20lot%20of%20my%20natural%20perimeters%20and%20protections%2C%20and%20it's%20dropped%20all%20of%20those%20walls%2C%26quot%3B%20Britton%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20attackers%20no%20longer%20have%20to%20%26quot%3Bbeat%20your%20firewall%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bget%20into%20your%20building.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETechnology%20is%20also%20much%20more%20deeply%20integrated%20into%20everyday%20life%20than%20it%20used%20to%20be%2C%20offering%20would-be%20attackers%20new%20devices%20to%20try%20to%20compromise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20old%20insider%20threat%20was%20the%20disgruntled%20employee%2C%26quot%3B%20Risley%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20new%20insider%20threat%20is%20the%20loyal%20employee%20with%20a%20compromised%20device.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22be4887ca-afe8-4387-b4b3-d968457ac1b2%5C%22%3E'It's%20a%20harder%20job%20than%20it%20was'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20growing%20gap%20in%20the%20workforce%20of%20about%204.8%20million%20cybersecurity%20jobs%20globally%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.isc2.org%2FInsights%2F2024%2F09%2FEmployers-Must-Act-Cybersecurity-Workforce-Growth-Stalls-as-Skills-Gaps-Widen%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20a%202024%20study%20from%20cybersecurity%20member%20association%20ISC2%20%E2%80%94%20a%2019%25%20year-over-year%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20cybersecurity%20risks%20become%20more%20sophisticated%2C%20the%20job%20has%20also%20become%20more%20challenging%2C%20industry%20executives%20told%20BI%2C%20which%20has%20made%20it%20difficult%20to%20meet%20the%20rising%20demand.%20Cybersecurity%20roles%20take%2021%25%20longer%20on%20average%20to%20fill%20than%20other%20jobs%20in%20the%20IT%20field%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cyberseek.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20data%20analytics%20firm%20Cyberseek.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20harder%20job%20than%20it%20was%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20Risley%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20just%20so%20many%20more%20protocols%2C%20so%20many%20more%20policies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMK%20Palmore%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20director%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-director-cybersecurity-jobs-in-demand-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20Cloud's%20office%20of%20the%20chief%20information%20security%20officer%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20previously%20told%20BI%20that%20many%20cybersecurity%20professionals%20started%20in%20IT%20and%20transitioned%20over.%20He%20said%20it%20can%20be%20difficult%20for%20a%20new%20candidate%20to%20get%20the%20needed%20hands-on%20experience%20in%20the%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchueler%2C%20who's%20been%20in%20the%20industry%20for%2025%20years%2C%20said%20cyberattacks%20are%20%26quot%3Bescalating%20at%20a%20pace%26quot%3B%20he's%20never%20seen.%20That's%20made%20it%20challenging%20for%20candidates%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20skills%20needed.%20He%20said%20an%20employee%20taking%20just%20three%20months%20off%20could%20face%20a%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20massive%26quot%3B%20knowledge%20gap%20upon%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stakes%20are%20also%20incredibly%20high.%20DNA-testing%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F23andme-what-went-wrong-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E23andMe%3C%2Fa%3E%20agreed%20to%20pay%20%2430%20million%20in%20September%20to%20settle%20a%20lawsuit%20after%20hackers%20accessed%20the%20personal%20data%20of%20millions%20of%20its%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20a%20software%20issue%20caused%20by%20cybersecurity%20firm%20CrowdStrike%20resulted%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-crowdstrike-outage-could-hurt-consumer-trust-big-tech-ai-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eglobal%20IT%20outage%20that%20disrupted%3C%2Fa%3E%20several%20industries%2C%20including%20airlines%2C%20banks%2C%20and%20emergency%20services.%20While%20the%20incident%20wasn't%20the%20result%20of%20a%20bad%20actor%20gaining%20access%20to%20a%20system%2C%20it's%20a%20testament%20to%20how%20integrated%20cybersecurity%20systems%20are%20within%20the%20tech%20that%20powers%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20companies%20like%20Cyderes%20or%20S-RM%20offer%20specialized%20training%20programs%2C%20smaller%20firms%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20provide%20that%20kind%20of%20programming.%20Risley%20told%20BI%20that%20his%20company%20doesn't%20usually%20hire%20recent%20graduates%2C%20and%20looks%20more%20for%20%26quot%3Bbattle-hardened%20cyber%20security%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20do%20happen%20to%20get%20a%20job%20in%20the%20field%20though%2C%20it%20may%20be%20worth%20holding%20onto.%20Schueler%20told%20BI%20the%20career%20path%20is%20here%20to%20stay%20%E2%80%94%20and%20will%20become%20increasingly%20important%20as%20technology%20evolves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20it%20tends%20to%20pay%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20top%20ranks%20of%20the%20profession%2C%20US-based%20CISOs%20make%20about%20%24565%2C000%20annually%2C%20with%20some%20exceeding%20%241%20million%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iansresearch.com%2Fresources%2Fpress-releases%2Fdetail%2Fnew-report-from-ians-research-and-artico-search-reveals-ciso-compensation-remains-strong-despite-2024-market-slowdown%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20an%20IANS%20Research%20and%20Artico%20Search%20report%20that%20includes%20data%20from%20over%20755%20CISOs%20between%20April%20and%20August%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchueler%20told%20BI%20that%20recent%20grads%20and%20seasoned%20professionals%20in%20cybersecurity%20can%20earn%20above-average%20salaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20industry%20does%20pay%20very%2C%20very%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-cybersecurity-jobs-high-demand-ai-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738059182000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6797fb0eeb4be2fff9a24dbc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-cybersecurity-jobs-high-demand-ai-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Cybersecurity%20executives%20explain%20how%20the%20threat%20landscape%20has%20evolved%20%E2%80%94%20and%20why%20it%20can%20be%20challenging%20to%20find%20the%20right%20talent.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-cybersecurity-jobs-high-demand-ai-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%