https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-targets-dei-mandates-federal-employees-day-one-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eending%20diversity%2C%20equity%2C%20and%20inclusion%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20federal%20government%2C%20the%20private%20sector's%20DEI%20efforts%20have%20come%20under%20heightened%20legal%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20order%20encourages%20the%20private%20sector%20to%20end%20%26quot%3Billegal%20DEI%20discrimination%20and%20preferences.%26quot%3B%20As%20part%20of%20that%20plan%2C%20the%20order%20tasks%20each%20federal%20agency%20to%20%26quot%3Bidentify%20up%20to%20nine%20potential%20civil%20compliance%20investigations%26quot%3B%20of%20enterprises%20including%20publicly%20traded%20corporations%20and%20large%20nonprofits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20current%20spotlight%20on%20DEI%20initiatives%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-day-one-agenda-executive-orders-inauguration-day-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump's%20executive%20actions%3C%2Fa%3E%20targeting%20them%2C%20employment%20attorneys%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20companies%20would%20be%20wise%20to%20assess%20their%20own%20diversity-related%20programs%20with%20legal%20counsel%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20are%20ironclad%20in%20the%20face%20of%20potential%20federal%20investigations%20or%20workplace%20lawsuits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20main%20thing%20that%20employers%20should%20be%20doing%20right%20now%20is%20conducting%20what%20we%20call%20either%20a%20DEI%20audit%20or%20a%20vulnerability%20assessment%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Michael%20Thomas%2C%20a%20California-based%20attorney%20specializing%20in%20corporate%20diversity%20practices%20at%20the%20law%20firm%20Jackson%20Lewis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20this%20type%20of%20assessment%2C%20companies%20would%20work%20with%20outside%20counsel%20to%20review%20their%20policies%20and%20practices%20related%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fdiversity-and-inclusion%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDEI%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20equal%20employment%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDEI%20initiatives%20that%20focus%20on%20the%20requirements%20of%20federal%20equal%20employment%20opportunity%20laws%20are%20most%20likely%20to%20be%20legally%20compliant%2C%20Thomas%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHiring%20quotas%20or%20preferential%20treatment%20to%20certain%20groups%20of%20people%20were%20already%20illegal%20and%20now%20pose%20a%20higher%20legal%20risk%2C%20Thomas%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20law%20hasn't%20changed%2C%26quot%3B%20Thomas%20said%2C%20explaining%2C%20however%2C%20%26quot%3BYour%20scrutiny%20has%20increased%2C%20the%20attention%20has%20increased%2C%20and%20you%20face%20potential%20legal%2C%20reputational%2C%20and%20brand%20risk%20from%20both%20your%20majority%2C%20for%20lack%20of%20a%20better%20phrase%2C%20and%20also%20your%20underrepresented%20groups.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJon%20Solorzano%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20the%20law%20firm%20Vinson%20%26amp%3B%20Elkins%2C%20told%20BI%20the%20legal%20grounds%20involving%20diversity%20initiatives%20haven't%20really%20changed%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20the%20risks%20have.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDEI%20initiatives%20are%20not%2C%20in%20and%20of%20themselves%2C%20problematic%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Solorzano%2C%20who%20advises%20public%20and%20private%20companies%20on%20areas%20related%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fesg-investing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EESG%3C%2Fa%3E%20(environmental%2C%20social%2C%20and%20governance)%20and%20risk%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20that%20there%20is%20more%20scrutiny%20on%20the%20acronym%20and%20now%20the%20full%20force%20of%20the%20federal%20government%20has%20squarely%20taken%20aim%20at%20this%20concept%2C%26quot%3B%20Solorzano%20said%20of%20DEI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESolorzano%20said%20that%20he%20has%20already%20spoken%20with%20numerous%20companies%20that%20have%20inquired%20about%20whether%20their%20DEI%20policies%20are%20compliant%20with%20the%20law%2C%20and%20what%2C%20if%20anything%2C%20they%20should%20do%20to%20change%20their%20practices%20to%20minimize%20their%20risks%20of%20being%20a%20target%20of%20an%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20executive%20order%20is%20almost%20certain%20to%20create%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20corporate%20DEI%20initiatives%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Solorzano%2C%20who%20added%20that%20he%20expects%20to%20see%20even%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftarget-ends-dei-initiatives-memo-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompanies%20roll%20back%20their%20DEI%20efforts%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225429%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22File%20photo%20of%20then-President%20Donald%20Trump%20signing%20an%20executive%20order.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664fce1da961b37edf398a6e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223620%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETrump%20signed%20a%20flurry%20of%20executive%20orders%20after%20taking%20office.%3Cp%3EReuters%2FJonathan%20Ernst%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThough%2C%20companies%20%26quot%3Bneed%20to%20be%20careful%20about%20clumsily%20nixing%20all%20initiatives%2C%26quot%3B%20Solorzano%20said.%20%26quot%3BPulling%20out%20of%20initiatives%2C%20just%20because%20it%20is%20politically%20disfavored%20at%20the%20moment%2C%20may%20not%20be%20the%20right%20thing%20for%20a%20business%20over%20the%20long%20term.%20But%20careful%20calibration%20of%20the%20risks%20and%20values%20of%20pursuing%20these%20initiatives%20remain%20critical.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDomenique%20Camacho%20Moran%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20the%20law%20firm%20Farrell%20Fritz%20in%20New%20York%2C%20also%20called%20it%20%26quot%3Bcritical%26quot%3B%20that%20every%20organization%20continues%20to%20evaluate%20its%20DEI-related%20policies%20to%20ensure%20they%20are%20not%20%26quot%3Bin%20the%20interest%20of%20doing%20something%20good%2C%20inadvertently%20crossing%20the%20line.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDEI%20programs%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-data-driven-strategies-tools-refine-dei-belonging-efforts-decisions-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%20companies%20have%20adopted%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20%26quot%3Boften%20talked%20about%20commitment%20to%20equal%20opportunity%26quot%3B%20and%20about%20%26quot%3Beducating%20the%20workforce%2C%26quot%3B%20Camacho%20Moran%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20rarely%20included%20numbers%20or%20targets%20for%20specific%20diversity%20initiatives.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20programs%2C%20however%2C%20%26quot%3Bwere%20not%20scrutinized%20closely%20by%20a%20variety%20of%20government%20agencies%2C%20and%20so%20some%20of%20those%20programs%20were%20outlined%20and%20articulated%20programming%20and%20opportunities%20that%20emphasized%20a%20particular%20minority%20group%20or%20particular%20protected%20class%2C%26quot%3B%20Camacho%20Moran%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttorneys%20told%20BI%20they%20now%20expect%2C%20due%20to%20the%20current%20political%20climate%2C%20employers%20to%20face%20an%20uptick%20of%20lawsuits%20alleging%20discrimination%20and%20so-called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-owes-11-million-fees-reverse-discrimination-case-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereverse%20discrimination%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20Woo%2C%20also%20an%20attorney%20at%20the%20firm%20Jackson%20Lewis%2C%20said%20it%20is%20likely%20employers%20will%20see%20a%20rise%20in%20internal%20complaints%20from%20employees%20who%20are%20for%20and%20against%20DEI%20initiatives%2C%20which%20will%20likely%20translate%20to%20more%20lawsuits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompanies%20should%20have%20a%20heightened%20sense%20of%20awareness%20now%20in%20terms%20of%20how%20to%20approach%20these%20because%20of%20the%20fact%20there%20will%20be%20more%20inquiries%2C%20more%20complaints%20internally%2C%26quot%3B%20Woo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThomas%20said%20there%20had%20been%20legal%20challenges%20to%20DEI%20programs%20since%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-ends-affirmative-action-colleges-decision-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court's%202023%20ruling%20ending%20affirmative%20action%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20college%20admissions%2C%20and%20expects%20those%20challenges%20to%20increase%20post%20Trump's%20executive%20actions%20taking%20aim%20at%20DEI%20initiatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERon%20Zambrano%2C%20the%20employment%20litigation%20chairman%20at%20the%20California%20law%20firm%20West%20Coast%20Trial%20Lawyers%2C%20told%20BI%20he%20also%20expects%20to%20see%20a%20rise%20in%20lawsuits%20related%20to%20companies'%20DEI%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20potential%20complaints%20may%20even%20cite%20Trump's%20executive%20order%20targeting%20DEI%20initiatives%20%26quot%3Bas%20a%20form%20of%20legitimacy%2C%26quot%3B%20Zambrano%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20possible%20lawsuits%20would%20succeed%20only%20%26quot%3Bif%20they%20would%20have%20succeeded%20regardless%20of%20Trump%20or%20Trump's%20executive%20order%2C%26quot%3B%20Zambrano%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20does%20happen.%20There%20is%20reverse%20discrimination.%20It%20absolutely%20does%20exist%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20as%20pervasive%20as%20just%2C%20like%2C%20well%2C%20the%20existence%20of%20DEI%20means%20that%20only%20minorities%20are%20going%20to%20have%20the%20advantage%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Zambrano.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20implication%2C%20right%3F%20That's%20the%20fear.%20That's%20the%20messaging.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-sector-companies-dei-diversity-practices-donald-trump-order-2025-1%5C%22