25-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecritisized%20the%20Federal%20Emergency%20Management%20Agency%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20%26quot%3Bslow%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bbureaucratic%2C%26quot%3B%20arguing%20it%20costs%20too%20much%20money%20and%20that%20states%20would%20do%20a%20better%20job%20handling%20disaster%20response.%20He's%20since%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fpresidential-actions%2F2025%2F01%2Fcouncil-to-assess-the-federal-emergency-management-agency%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eissued%20an%20executive%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%20directing%20a%20%26quot%3Bfull-scale%20review%26quot%3B%20of%20FEMA%20as%20a%20first%20step%20to%20either%20overhauling%20or%20eliminating%20the%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20president's%20threat%20comes%20as%20FEMA%20responds%20to%20an%20increasing%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-climate-change-crisis-extreme-weather-is-costing-you-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecatastrophic%20disasters%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Thousands%20of%20FEMA%20workers%20are%20spread%20out%20across%20places%20like%20LA%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20and%20Georgia%20and%20tasked%20with%20delivering%20financial%20aid%20to%20people%20displaced%20by%20wildfires%2C%20hurricanes%2C%20flooding%2C%20and%20tornadoes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Republican%20and%20Democratic%20officials%20have%20warned%20the%20agency%20is%20stretched%20too%20thin%20and%20have%20also%20proposed%20states%20take%20on%20a%20greater%20share%20of%20preparedness%20and%20response.%20Already%2C%20state%20and%20local%20governments%20lead%20their%20own%20disaster%20recovery%20efforts%20and%20ask%20FEMA%20to%20step%20in%20when%20they%20lack%20enough%20resources%20to%20handle%20it%20themselves.%20After%20the%20president%20approves%20a%20disaster%20declaration%20request%20from%20a%20governor%2C%20FEMA%20mobilizes%20a%20national%20response%20that%20involves%20coordinating%20with%20other%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThink%20of%20FEMA%20as%20the%20quarterback%20for%20the%20federal%20government's%20response.%20But%20this%20is%20all%20in%20support%20of%20the%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20Daniel%20Kaniewski%2C%20who%20served%20as%20the%20second-highest%20ranking%20official%20at%20FEMA%20during%20Trump's%20first%20term%2C%20said.%20FEMA%20helps%20fund%20both%20short-term%20emergency%20response%20and%20longer-term%20recovery%20for%20months%20%E2%80%94%20and%20in%20some%20cases%20years%20%E2%80%94%20after%20a%20disaster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20president%20alone%20also%20can't%20eliminate%20FEMA%2C%20which%20would%20require%20Congress%20to%20change%20several%20laws.%20Trump's%20executive%20order%20established%20a%20FEMA%20review%20council%20co-chaired%20by%20the%20secretaries%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20and%20Defense.%20The%20council%20is%20tasked%20with%20evaluating%20the%20agency's%20disaster%20response%20during%20the%20past%20four%20years%20and%20comparing%20it%20to%20efforts%20by%20state%20and%20local%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Senate%20has%20confirmed%20former%20South%20Dakota%20Gov.%20Kristi%20Noem%20to%20lead%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20and%20Pete%20Hegseth%20to%20lead%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense.%20Trump%20hasn't%20nominated%20a%20FEMA%20administrator%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20look%20at%20FEMA's%20budget%20and%20role%20during%20a%20natural%20disaster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2223f21575-560f-4c88-9a42-0902889fbb6b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFEMA%20has%20three%20main%20assistance%20programs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20said%20it%20employs%20more%20than%2020%2C000%20people%20nationwide%2C%20including%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20and%20across%2010%20regional%20offices%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dhs.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-04%2F2024_0320_federal_emergency_management_agency.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20a%20%2433%20billion%20budget%3C%2Fa%3E%20appropriated%20by%20Congress.%20The%20vast%20majority%20of%20that%20budget%20is%20for%20the%20Disaster%20Relief%20Fund%2C%20the%20primary%20account%20that%20pays%20for%20the%20government's%20response%20and%20recovery%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20president%20approves%20a%20disaster%20declaration%2C%20FEMA%20has%20the%20authority%20to%20offer%20a%20range%20of%20financial%20aid%20to%20governments%20and%20individuals.%20These%20programs%20are%20known%20as%20public%2C%20hazard%20mitigation%2C%20and%20individual%20assistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFEMA%20typically%20reimburses%20state%20and%20local%20governments%20for%2075%25%20of%20the%20costs%20of%20handling%20a%20disaster%20and%20long-term%20recovery.%20These%20costs%20can%20include%20debris%20removal%2C%20search%20and%20rescue%2C%20emergency%20transportation%2C%20distributing%20food%20and%20first%20aid%2C%20and%20rebuilding%20public%20infrastructure.%20FEMA%20also%20issues%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20grants%20to%20state%20and%20local%20governments%20for%20projects%20that%20harden%20communities%20against%20future%20disasters%2C%20such%20as%20enforcing%20stronger%20building%20codes%2C%20building%20sea%20walls%2C%20and%20upgrading%20stormwater%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDisaster%20survivors%20can%20apply%20for%20individual%20assistance%2C%20which%20is%20largely%20targeted%20at%20the%20uninsured%20or%20underinsured.%20FEMA%20grants%20can%20cover%20temporary%20housing%2C%20rental%20assistance%2C%20home%20repairs%2C%20unemployment%20benefits%2C%20and%20in%20some%20cases%20legal%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFEMA%20doesn't%20allow%20for%20duplication%20of%20benefits%2C%20so%20if%20your%20insurance%20paid%20for%20something%2C%20then%20you%20can't%20get%20reimbursed%20by%20the%20federal%20government%2C%26quot%3B%20Kaniewski%2C%20now%20a%20managing%20director%20at%20Marsh%20McLennan%2C%20a%20consulting%20firm%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFEMA%20said%20it%20has%20provided%20more%20than%20%24316%20million%20in%20grants%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhurricane-helene-couple-lost-home-livelihood-home-insurance-medical-bills-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHurricane%20Helene%20survivors%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20North%20Carolina%20alone%2C%20including%20more%20than%20%246.2%20million%20in%20rental%20assistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20FEMA%20also%20started%20offering%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fema.gov%2Fpress-release%2F20240119%2Fbiden-harris-administration-reforms-disaster-assistance-program-help%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bserious%20needs%20assistance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20%24750%20grant%20helps%20cover%20disaster%20survivors's%20emergency%20expenses%20such%20as%20evacuation%2C%20food%2C%20and%20shelter.%20The%20new%20grant%20was%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20set%20of%20changes%20aimed%20at%20streamlining%20individual%20assistance%20after%20long-standing%20complaints%20from%20disaster%20survivors%20that%20the%20process%20took%20too%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ebb94331-7838-46a2-ad35-4a02515453a1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFEMA%20leaders%20say%20it's%20strapped%20for%20resources%20and%20that%20states%20could%20take%20on%20more%20responsibility%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECongress%20is%20unlikely%20to%20eliminate%20FEMA%20altogether.%20However%2C%20several%20former%20FEMA%20leaders%20have%20raised%20concerns%20that%20the%20agency%20is%20stretched%20too%20thin%20and%20proposed%20that%20states%20do%20more%20to%20prepare%20and%20respond%20to%20disasters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20October%202022%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffema-helene-milton-relief-funding-congress-disaster-victims-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFEMA%20has%20regularly%20projected%20shortfalls%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Disaster%20Relief%20Fund%2C%20in%20part%20because%20the%20agency%20is%20responding%20to%20a%20rising%20number%20of%20hurricanes%2C%20floods%2C%20wildfires%2C%20and%20other%20disasters.%20Scientists%20warn%20are%20becoming%20more%20frequent%20and%20destructive%20due%20to%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20Between%20fiscal%20years%201988%20and%201997%2C%20there%20were%20an%20average%20of%2039%20major%20disaster%20declarations.%20In%20the%20most%20recent%20decade%2C%20there%20were%20an%20average%20of%2063%2C%20an%20increase%20of%2061%25%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fsearch%3Fq%3Dcongressional%2Bresearch%2Bservice%26rlz%3D1C5GCEM_en%26oq%3Dcongressional%2Bresea%26gs_lcrp%3DEgZjaHJvbWUqCggAEAAYsQMYgAQyCggAEAAYsQMYgAQyBwgBEAAYgAQyBwgCEAAYgAQyBwgDEAAYgAQyBggEEEUYOTIHCAUQABiABDIHCAYQABiABDIHCAcQABiABDIHCAgQABiABDIHCAkQABiABNIBCDI1MTdqMGo3qAIAsAIA%26sourceid%3Dchrome%26ie%3DUTF-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECongressional%20Research%20Service%20found%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresidents%20have%20also%20expanded%20FEMA's%20mandate%20beyond%20responding%20to%20weather-related%20disasters%20%E2%80%94%20further%20taxing%20its%20resources.%20The%20agency%20in%20recent%20years%20has%20helped%20local%20governments%20respond%20to%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%20and%20an%20increasing%20number%20of%20unaccompanied%20children%20crossing%20the%20southern%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration%20may%20look%20to%20Project%202025%2C%20a%20policy%20agenda%20published%20by%20the%20conservative%20think%20tank%20Heritage%20Foundation%2C%20for%20ideas%20to%20shift%20more%20costs%20to%20the%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.project2025.org%2F2025_MandateForLeadership_CHAPTER-05.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esection%20on%20FEMA%3C%2Fa%3E%20calls%20on%20Congress%20to%20change%20the%20cost-share%20arrangement%20so%20that%20the%20federal%20government%20covers%2025%25%20of%20the%20costs%20for%20small%20disasters.%20But%20for%20%26quot%3Btruly%20catastrophic%26quot%3B%20disasters%2C%20the%20threshold%20should%20be%20capped%20at%2075%25%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProject