th%20PM%20Modi%2C%20the%20first%20interaction%20between%20the%20leaders%20after%20the%20former%20took%20oath%20as%20the%2047th%20President%20of%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Trump%20also%20told%20reporters%20that%20he%20discussed%20the%20issue%20of%20illegal%20Indian%20immigrants%20in%20the%20US%20with%20PM%20Modi%2C%20expressing%20confidence%20that%20the%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20will%20do%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20is%20right%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20matter%2C%20underlining%20that%20discussions%20are%20going%20on%20with%20India%20on%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20in%20a%20readout%20of%20a%20phone%20call%20between%20both%20leaders%2C%20the%20White%20House%20said%20that%20Trump%20had%20sought%20a%20move%20towards%20a%20%26quot%3Bfair%26quot%3B%20bilateral%20trading%20relationship%20and%20deeper%20India-US%20cooperation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia-US%20Relations%20Under%20Trump's%201st%20Presidency%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20enjoyed%20a%20comfortable%20relationship%20with%20the%20United%20States%20during%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20first%20term%20in%20the%20White%20House.%20The%20Republican%20also%20shared%20some%20remarkable%20similarities%20in%20his%20style%20and%20slogans%20with%20PM%20Modi%2C%20especially%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20their%20rhetoric%20of%20making%20their%20nations%20great%20again%2C%20contributing%20to%20their%20strong%20personal%20relations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20leaders%20addressed%20thousands%20of%20people%20at%20two%20different%20rallies%20in%20Houston%20in%20September%202019%20and%20in%20Ahmedabad%20in%20February%202020.%20PM%20Modi%20was%20among%20the%20top%20three%20world%20leaders%20to%20speak%20with%20Mr%20Trump%20after%20his%20stunning%20electoral%20victory%20in%20November%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20Administration%20between%202017-21%20saw%20the%20revival%20of%20the%20moribund%20Quadrilateral%20Security%20Forum%20(Quad)-%20which%20brings%20the%20US%2C%20Australia%2C%20India%2C%20and%20Japan%20together%20to%20work%20for%20a%20free%2C%20open%2C%20prosperous%20and%20inclusive%20Indo-Pacific%20region.%20His%20administration%20also%20remained%20America's%20oldest%20and%20largest%20military%20command%20-%20the%20Pacific%20Command%20-%20to%20Indo-Pacific%20Command%2C%20in%20a%20largely%20symbolic%20move%20to%20signal%20India's%20importance%20to%20the%20US%20military%20to%20counter%20China's%20militarisation%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Trump%2C%20the%20US%20National%20Security%20Strategy%20stressed%20that%20%26quot%3BIndo-Pacific%26quot%3B%20stretched%20%26quot%3Bfrom%20the%20west%20coast%20of%20India%20to%20the%20western%20shores%20of%20the%20United%20States%26quot%3B.%20This%20articulation%20of%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20framework%20provided%20a%20solid%20regional%20anchor%20for%20India-US%20cooperation%20for%20the%20first%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Trump's%20foreign%20policies%20were%20mostly%20carried%20forward%20by%20the%20Biden%20Administration%2C%20which%20doubled%20down%20on%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20strategy%20and%20saw%20India%20as%20its%20regional%20partner%20in%20securing%20a%20balance%20of%20power%20in%20Asia%20and%20its%20waters.%20There%20was%20little%20reason%20to%20believe%20the%20situation%20would%20be%20different%20during%20Trump%202.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Could%20Change%20Under%20Trump%202.0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20during%20his%20campaign%20for%20re-election%2C%20The%2078-year-old%20Republican%20called%20India%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20big%20abuser%26quot%3B%20on%20trade%20and%20vowed%20to%20use%20tariffs%20on%20global%20imports%20into%20the%20US%20to%20correct%20imbalances.%20He%20also%20threatened%20the%20BRICS%20group%20of%20nations%2C%20of%20which%20India%20is%20a%20part%2C%20with%20tariffs%20if%20they%20did%20not%20accept%20his%20demand%20of%20committing%20to%20not%20create%20a%20new%20currency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgain%20while%20talking%20to%20House%20Republicans%20at%20a%20Florida%20retreat%20on%20Monday%2C%20he%20said%20that%20the%20US%20would%20impose%20tariffs%20on%20the%20countries%20that%20%26quot%3Bharm%26quot%3B%20America%20as%20he%20named%20China%2C%20India%20and%20Brazil%20as%20high-tariff%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20his%20tariff%20threats%20aside%2C%20Mr%20Trump's%20second%20term%20is%20expected%20to%20bring%20both%20continuity%20and%20change%20in%20his%20India%20policies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20is%20India's%20largest%20trading%20partner%20and%20two-way%20trade%20surpassed%20%24118%20billion%20in%202023%2F24%2C%20with%20India%20posting%20a%20surplus%20of%20%2432%20billion.%20India%20is%20also%20an%20important%20strategic%20partner%20in%20US%20efforts%20to%20counter%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Monday's%20call%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20he%20%26quot%3Bemphasized%20the%20importance%20of%20India%20increasing%20its%20procurement%20of%20American-made%20security%20equipment%20and%20moving%20toward%20a%20fair%20bilateral%20trading%20relationship%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20White%20House%20statement%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20also%20said%20that%20Mr%20Trump%20and%20Mr%20Modi%20emphasized%20their%20commitment%20to%20the%20Quad%2C%20with%20India%20to%20host%20Quad%20leaders%20later%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20plays%20an%20important%20role%20in%20making%20the%20US%20a%20pre-eminent%20global%20power.%20Its%20tech%20industry%20majorly%20relies%20on%20Indian%20workers%20trained%20in%20science%2C%20technology%2C%20engineering%2C%20and%20mathematics%20(STEM)%20who%20move%20to%20the%20US%20with%20the%20help%20of%20H-1B%20visas.%20In%202023%2C%20Indian%20professionals%20constituted%20over%20a%20fourth%20of%20the%203.5%20million%20STEM%20workers%20in%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Trump%20has%20pledged%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20illegal%20immigration%2C%20but%20he%20said%20he